---
description: Priority order to resolve rule conflicts deterministically
alwaysApply: true
---

# Rule Priority (highest to lowest)

1. safety, security, and no-provenance-trace policy
2. explicit user request in current chat
3. session toggle state (`tiggreeeon` / `tiggreeeoff`)
4. enterprise release policy (only when release is requested)
5. architecture and design quality rules
6. token-efficiency and style preferences

# Conflict Resolution

- If two rules conflict, apply the higher-priority rule and continue.
- If user request conflicts with priority item 1, keep priority item 1 and explain briefly.
- Keep conflict explanations one or two lines maximum.
